column11: [{"value":"Private room has access to plenty of outside spaces and a pool. Behind a house in a private, gated subdivision, located right off of a busy street complete with grocery stores, restaurants, and easy access to New Orleans. Queen size bed. Best for couples or close friends as the bathroom is not completely separate from the bedroom section. Access to private patio and other seating areas in the backyard. Pool access is also available 24/7. We live in the main house so we will be happy to answer any questions and help out our guests in any way that we can. We also enjoy our pool and backyard regularly, so we will definitely be around. Gated neighborhood located off of a busy street with access to grocery stores, restaurants, and department stores. About 15-20 minutes drive to New Orleans. Driving is the best way to get around, or take a Lyft or an Uber. Smoking is allowed, but only in the outdoor spaces. Also.... See the pictures. Tub, toilet, and bed are in close proximity so this is best for couples or close friends that wouldn't mind sharing such a small space.","sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-21T21:43:00.000Z"}]

The bath mat was visibly dirty and needed cleaning. The floor in the “room” needed to be swept. A bed placed into a bathroom is what this “room” felt like. Loud ac unit hanging right above your head. Actually did not even stay the night. Within the hour, we left the keys where we found them and checked into a hotel. It was so bad that we lost out on 200 bucks and paid more to stay at a nice, clean place. A place where we showered immediately because the “room” was THAT bad. I do not recommend unless you like that kind of environment. The neighborhood and the host’s home were beautiful. But the garage is detached and the “room” you’re in is far from beautiful, clean, comfortable, or cozy.","username":"Stephanie"},{"date":"2019-10-07T19:39:17.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T21:43:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"This place is great! Amazing amenities for a reasonable price! Luxury on a budget.","username":"Imani"},{"date":"2018-07-05T21:46:38.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"Brooke is an amazing host. She provided all the instructions during check-in (gate code, WiFi password, keys, suggestions on restaurants, etc). Responses were quick and informative. Her place is cozy, super clean, quiet, and very private. The gated community is very beautiful and safe. The bed was super soft and comfortable providing a great night’s sleep! There are many decorative touches throughout the space and plenty of books to read! Overall, this is a great place to stay and the value is amazing! Definitely plan to stay here again. :)","username":"Roxanna"},{"date":"2019-09-20T17:27:45.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T21:43:00.000Z","rating":2.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"Her home itself is lovely and she is pretty nice. Though the room you stay in is literally just a full size mattress. Had Issues with lizards as soon as we came. We told her the issues ASAP and she kind of laughed it off. Place wasn’t the cleanest, there were fake lashes on a table that were old and hair all on the little bit of floor accessible. My fiancé and I canceled in 3-5 hours of being there and our stay was supposed to be for 3 nights I wasted money because she gave no refund; super strict policy — it makes sense because nobody wants to stay in that tiny room that you cant stand in. Horrible experience with attempting to get a refund so thats $200 in the trash.","username":"Miracle"},{"date":"2019-09-01T20:25:22.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T21:43:00.000Z","rating":3.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"Decent overall, slight adjustments like towels and small concern of air filtration. Convenient commute to downtown. Shopping nearby as well. Great community and gated is a plus.","username":"Quinn"},{"date":"2019-01-21T22:06:03.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"It was pretty cold in there, but otherwise a great experience","username":"Helen"},{"date":"2018-09-03T18:07:57.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"My fiancé and I came to New Orleans for a mini vacay and found Brooke’s cozy space perfect for us! We were out and about all throughout the day and knowing our space was detached from the main house made us feel more comfortable with our excursions. The room was private, cozy, and always kept cool. It was just what we needed after a day of adventure. Added bonus was being in a secure, quiet gated community. If you’re considering traveling to NOLA (with maybe one other person,) I would highly recommend staying at Brooke’s. The proximity to different areas was unbeatable and if you’re looking for a place to lay your head after a long, exciting day, this is the place. Thanks again, Brooke. Side Note: there were lots of pillows, extra blankets, towels, a television, and a bookcase filled with wonders.","username":"Gennavonah"},{"date":"2018-07-23T20:22:48.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"Amazon value and great hosts. I'll stay here again! Book this place instead of the high hotel prices during major weekends","username":"Maurice"},{"date":"2019-05-31T21:53:04.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"Very beautiful place to stay , very private and secure, very clean and is just as they said on the add so i really enjoy it...","username":"Luis"},{"date":"2018-09-16T21:55:20.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"Everything you need for a quick couple get away.Very close to everything you would want to do in the big easy","username":"Jern"},{"date":"2019-03-11T21:56:29.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:56:00.000Z","rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/25509776"],"text":"This room is located behind a beautiful home tucked away in a lovely gated community. My girlfriend and I felt safe and secure our entire stay. Additionally, it’s near many shops and restaurants and isn’t very far from the heart of New Orleans (about 20 minutes). Like other reviews mentioned, the room is tiny - about the size of a single dorm room. However, it’s a good fit for those traveling alone or with a significant other. I’m not sure if the listing mentioned this, but the room also has a mini fridge and a microwave which was a great surprise! Lastly, but certainly not least, Antoinette was a great host. She did a wonderful job of attending to our needs and answering any questions we had. This room is decent find for the price.","username":"Ashley"}]

It's in a guiet neighborhood about 10-15 minutes from the french quarter ($15-17 by Uber/Lyft). The value is really good for the price; you can't beat that. The only thing really missing, in my opinion, was a table for eating and some chairs to sit on. She let us use some little folding chairs from the back yard, but actual chairs would have been nice. Communication with Vanessa was great. She's very responsive and quick to reply. I'dconsider staying here again if in the area.","username":"Jim"},{"date":"2019-04-17T20:48:56.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T21:39:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/32018327"],"text":"Awesome cottage in a fantastic location. There is a huge fridge and a full stove/oven... perfect to buy your own food and save a couple bucks after a night out. Didn’t have a microwave, but anytime I needed hot water for the cup of noodles or mac n cheese I would just use the hot water from the keruig available! Beds are super comfy with lots of blankets and extra pillows if you need them! Vanessa was super helpful throughout the entire trip. We got in a little after check in and she was super cool about it, and gave us suggestions anytime we asked what are some cool things to do around the city. Anytime we had a question we got a response within a few minutes. Only about a 15 minute and 15 dollar Uber/Lyft drive from Bourbon St, French Quarter, and Mardi Gras world. We had a super late check in from a super late flight (2 am) he was totally flexible with it but hard to contact. We had our own key and he told us not to worry about making noise or being loud. The private bedroom was simple and clean with a tv and dvd movies. He had fridge space for our items and had no issue with us using the kitchen or utensils some of which were hard to find without introduction or non existent (silverware, pans, oven mit, trash, ect) . The bathroom is shared, definitely bring your own soap, it was not provided. All his personal items were out in the bathroom. We had to look around for towels ( no introduction). The bathroom floor mat was a folded towel. Floors and toilet could have used deeper cleaning. The shower head is really nice. Transportation to NOLA was super easy, there's a bus stop right out side the complex that takes you right into NOLA for cheap, takes like an hour. Uber works well too and is more time effective but is quite more pricey. There's also the ferry in Algiers that takes you right into the french q. for $2 each way. We agreed on a 10am checkout, but had no instruction on what to do with the key and he wasn't home so we left the key inside and left.","username":"Lilly"},{"date":"2019-02-24T20:50:57.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-21T20:57:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/17795902"],"text":"He will answer an questions ahead of time. column11: [{"value":"The perfect country home and ranch property. Near Central College in Pella, Iowa, the famous Sprint Car National Raceway in Knoxville, and just a few miles from Lake Red Rock. This property and surrounding area offers exceptional hiking, fishing and bird watching. The Harvey Happy Ranch offers it all! My home is 10 minutes from Pella, Iowa. during winter months i will be staying in the house and sharing kitchen and laundry, My home is spacious and comfortable. I have lived here since 1963. It has a real lived in feeling. The bedroom is large and airy. The private bath has plenty of hot water in the shower and all the towels are new. Endless coffee or tea in the kitchen. Kitchen is open to be used by guests. Visitors may use the whole house and property except one small bedroom. I will be sleeping elsewhere on the property. There is a barn with 1 mule, Cocoa, that is gentle for petting. An Australian Shepherd dog and a cat are also roaming the ranch. A very old log cabin is on the property. Access to Des Moines river 2 miles from house for hiking, fishing, and bird watching. Kitchen and laundry are always available. I would like to visit with my guests over coffee, tea, or wine if they wish. I have lived here many years and can be a resource for visitors. I know when folks enjoy their privacy and I will stay in my camper. Harvey is a small town. Harvey used to be a railroad crossroads but is now a bedroom town. There is no zoning here and a few eyesore properties. My neighbors are great people who would do anything to be helpful. To be in Harvey you need a car. No public transportation. It is safe to walk and jog here. I am 10 minutes from Knoxville and Pella. I work in Des Moines and it is 40 minutes to airport and 50 minutes to down town. I welcome all people to my home. Beautiful space, clean and unique. Great communication. A great place to relax. It was nice to have the space to cook. Looking forward to another stay if the opportunity arises.","username":"Trudi"},{"date":"2019-05-29T21:15:04.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-10-20T17:58:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/22666298"],"text":"Jeannie’s place was absolutely enchanting! My husband had to work on a nearby electrical project for a week for long hours, which left me and my cattle dog (Penny) on our own during the day without a vehicle. But instead of feeling lonely and bored, it was like being at a peaceful, spiritual retreat. Penny and I loved sitting on the porch listening to a symphony of songbirds. Multiple orioles and catbirds came to the feeder, and a sweet little wren came in and out of its quirky little home above a life-sized metal knight. The house was warm and inviting, with so many fascinating and interesting items on the walls. I told my husband that this was a home that is a testament to a life lived well. Jeannie has much to be proud of. She is clearly an interesting person with a wonderful story. Penny and I also had a wonderful time exploring the property. Don’t expect a sterile suburban cookie cutter environment. I loved the wilderness feel and the eclectic artifacts scattered about, including an authentic rough hewn log cabin, and an ancient airplane. Harvey is a tiny town of 277 people (according to the town sign), and Penny and I enjoyed walking every single street in the town over three days, and also biking out to the train trestle bridge on the outskirts of town. It was so interesting to see all of the different homes, most humble, but many clearly loved and maintained, often with quirky fun touches. The people we met on our wanderings were unfailingly warm and welcoming. Bob and I even stopped in “Peggy’s Place,” the only bar in town, and had the best time talking with the locals, who clearly enjoyed hearing about our upstate New York lifestyle, and gave us great recommendations. column50: Overview/ Rules: - Parties, pets, or smoking are prohibited. - Please keep the volume low (especially after 11p). - Put trash in receptacles. - Please tidy up after yourselves in shared areas (Family room, bathroom, kitchen). - We will not be providing food, but you will have access to the kitchen and refrigerator to store things cook. You can help yourself to anything in the main fridge. (Freezer is off limits.) - Anything sitting on the counter or table in the kitchen (coffee, tea, creamer, etc), please help yourself! Keep in mind: - Food, drinks (except for water), and shoes are not permitted upstairs, as the carpet is very light. - The master bedroom, formal living room, and formal dining room are NOT shared areas and are off limits. - BBQing or cooking outside is prohibited. - Please do not consume any of the alcohol located on the bar in the family room.
